  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "`--wsorigins \"*\"` throws CORS error when I call geth from my browser in a local file. Tried running geth on same computer and different computer.\r\n\r\n`geth --syncmode light  --ws --ws.api eth,net,web3 --wsorigins \"*\"`\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2020-09-15 03-45-58](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4725003/93181121-10169000-f706-11ea-8e29-db291eaf3942.png)\r\n\r\nI tried `--http.corsdomain '*'` and that works properly not throwing a CORS error.  \r\nHTTP shows all domains allowed but WSS is blank:\r\n![Screenshot from 2020-09-15 04-13-34](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4725003/93184111-de9fc380-f709-11ea-9440-b770e6fca4d4.png)\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.9.14-stable\r\nGit Commit: 6d74d1e5f762e06a6a739a42261886510f842778\r\nGit Commit Date: 20200513\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [65 64 63]\r\nGo Version: go1.14.2\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/home/travis/.gimme/versions/go1.14.2.linux.amd64\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nNo CORS errors\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nCORS error\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nRun geth with ws \r\n\r\nRun this html/js\r\n```\r\n<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"./web3.min.js\"></script>\r\n   <script type=\"text/javascript\">\r\n       window.web3 = new Web3(new Web3.providers.HttpProvider(\"ws://localhost:8546\"));\r\n  </script>\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
